{
  "text": "Although it remains unclear whether these agents truly operate by altering the microenvironmental availability of Trp and Kyn [CITATION_1] , the antineoplastic effects of IDO inhibitors critically rely on the host immune system, implying that this constitutes an instance of active anticancer immunotherapy [CITATION_2] . This also applies to strategies aimed at limiting the extracellular availability of adenosine.",
